metadata.name: #01 | Curiosity
metadata.description:
The curiosity in his eyes looking into my camera reflects how my eyes look back at the world.

I could tell he wondered what all the buttons and gadgets did. He had so many questions about what I did and how the camera worked. I could see his eyes light up with every new piece of information I gave him. I am ready for my own eyes to light up as I open myself up to the world.

Many go from the cradle to grave without ever truly living. On this day, I learned to live. 

Have a walk with me through San Juan.
